<p class="p">Indicators for each variable (or grouped variables) were ranked in classes according to their values using the
 <italic class="italic"> K</italic>-means method. The indices were then standardized to vary from zero (less vulnerable) to one (more vulnerable) using the following general formula: 
 <disp-formula id="eq1" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(1)</label>
  <math id="M1" class="math">
   <mtable style="T1" class="mtable">
    <mtr class="mtr">
     <mtd class="mtd">
      <mi class="mi">I</mi>
      <mi class="mi">p</mi>
      <mo class="mo">=</mo>
      <mfrac class="mfrac">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">I</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">o</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">b</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">s</mi>
        <mo class="mo">−</mo>
        <mi class="mi">I</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">m</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">i</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">n</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">I</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">m</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">a</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">x</mi>
        <mo class="mo">−</mo>
        <mi class="mi">I</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">m</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">i</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">n</mi>
       </mrow>
      </mfrac>
      <mo class="mo">,</mo>
     </mtd>
    </mtr>
   </mtable>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>Where 
 <italic class="italic">Ip</italic> is standardized index, 
 <italic class="italic">I</italic>obs is calculated index (for each municipality), 
 <italic class="italic">I</italic>max is maximum value of the index among all municipalities, and 
 <italic class="italic">I</italic>min is minimum value of the index among all municipalities.
</p>
